    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="9">
            <title>Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install the power steering idler shaft into the rear cover by making sure
                    the idler shaft bore is clean.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px"/>
                <caption>Install retaining ring on the idler shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a retaining ring on the end of the shaft that does not have the threaded hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Idler shaft and retaining ring in the Power Steering Idler Shaft Installation Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the idler shaft in the Power Steering Idler Shaft Installation Tool . Place the
                    end with the threaded hole in the tool first. This tool is designed to install the idler shaft in
                    the rear cover at the proper height.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD16/D1619.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 474. Power steering idler shaft in transmission side of rear cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler shaft</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Idler shaft in the rear cover assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow the retaining ring to contact the rear cover. Contact
                        may distort the retaining ring, adversely affecting its performance as a gear thrust surface.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the idler shaft in the rear cover at the proper location. Using the installation
                    tool, drive the idler shaft in the idler shaft bore in the transmission side of the rear cover,
                    until the installation tool bottoms out.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd16/D1618.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation height of power steering idler shaft</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler shaft</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If installation tool is not available, use brass drift to install the idler shaft in the
                    rear cover to the correct height.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Verify idler shaft height</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify idler shaft height, using a dial caliper. Idler shaft height should be 34.6
                    &#177; 0.15 mm (1.362 &#177; 0.006 in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install new dowel pins in crankcase if pins are damaged or
                        missing.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2351320" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 475. Application of Sealant</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) at the ends, where the crankcase and the lower crankcase meet.
                    Apply liquid gasket to the hydraulic oil pump cover joint, if the cover was not removed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device or get help to install the
                        rear cover.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651321" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0607.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 476. Rear cover assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear cover assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651326" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD06/D06150.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 477. Rear cover mounting bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked A, (M10 x 55) (5)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked B, (M10 x 70) (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts marked C, (M10 x 60) (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install eleven mounting bolts into the rear cover. See illustration for size and
                    location. Tighten all bolts to the standard torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
